WEBVTT

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:39.560
Mom.

00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:40.840
You're back.

00:01:41.160 --> 00:01:41.720
Yeah, I'm back.

00:01:42.760 --> 00:01:44.840
What are you doing? Let me help.

00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:46.880
No need.

00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:48.520
Making me something tasty again?

00:01:52.520 --> 00:01:53.200
Mom.

00:01:53.840 --> 00:01:54.360
This...

00:01:56.280 --> 00:01:56.840
Mom.

00:01:57.840 --> 00:01:59.880
What's this supposed to mean?

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:02.000
Xuan Yao.

00:02:02.760 --> 00:02:06.240
You and Zhang Du should stay at the old house for now.

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:08.919
Your dad's so stubborn.

00:02:09.080 --> 00:02:10.280
You know how he is.

00:02:10.280 --> 00:02:11.360
Just ignore him.

00:02:12.200 --> 00:02:12.720
Also...

00:02:13.480 --> 00:02:15.440
Don't go to the factory for a while.

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:17.400
You said it yourself anyway.

00:02:17.400 --> 00:02:18.720
You two just can't get along.

00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:21.920
Fine, that works.

00:02:22.320 --> 00:02:24.840
I could use some peace and quiet.

00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:27.600
Your clothes and things you need,

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:29.120
I packed them all in the suitcase.

00:02:29.120 --> 00:02:30.200
If you need anything else,

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:32.200
Just call me and I'll bring it over.

00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:32.760
Okay.

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:33.200
Mom.

00:02:33.480 --> 00:02:34.800
The stuff in my room,

00:02:35.080 --> 00:02:36.920
I'll pack it all up and send it to you later.

00:02:36.920 --> 00:02:38.360
I knew my mom understands me best.

00:02:40.760 --> 00:02:41.360
All right.

00:02:42.360 --> 00:02:45.000
Every family has its own troubles.

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:46.640
Oh right, Mom.

00:02:47.160 --> 00:02:49.080
I've been working at the drying yard,

00:02:49.560 --> 00:02:50.720
And earned 30,000 yuan.

00:02:51.280 --> 00:02:52.840
I put it all on a bank card.

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:55.360
The password is your birthday.

00:02:55.440 --> 00:02:56.360
I'll give it to you in a bit.

00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:57.440
That much?

00:02:57.440 --> 00:02:58.280
It's not that much.

00:02:58.320 --> 00:02:59.280
If I had a bit more time,

00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:00.360
I could earn even more.

00:03:00.640 --> 00:03:02.360
It can't cover anything major,

00:03:02.440 --> 00:03:05.320
But it'll help in an emergency.

00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:07.720
No need, you keep it.

00:03:07.720 --> 00:03:09.040
Why are you being so polite?

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:10.600
All right.

00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:11.840
Here, Mom.

00:03:14.080 --> 00:03:16.440
Son, really, keep it for yourself.

00:03:16.440 --> 00:03:17.800
Mom, why are you being so polite?

00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:19.840
Mom, just take it, take it.

00:03:20.080 --> 00:03:21.000
Take it, Mom.

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:22.280
This is for you.

00:03:22.640 --> 00:03:24.000
Don't tell my dad though.

00:03:24.280 --> 00:03:26.080
If he wants to worry, let him.

00:03:26.080 --> 00:03:28.200
Just don't get yourself worked up too.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:30.600
Okay.

00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:32.800
I'll keep it for you.

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:34.000
Once it blows over...

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:36.640
Eat well, drink well.

00:03:36.920 --> 00:03:37.920
Don't stay up late.

00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:40.360
Got it, Mom.

00:03:45.680 --> 00:03:47.360
I'm off, bye.

00:04:01.280 --> 00:04:02.480
Since we caught those two last time

00:04:02.480 --> 00:04:03.520
Who were illegally dumping wastewater,

00:04:03.560 --> 00:04:04.880
No one dares to do it anymore.

00:04:05.520 --> 00:04:06.600
Throughout the entire town,

00:04:06.600 --> 00:04:09.760
There are over a hundred Xuan paper mills.

00:04:09.880 --> 00:04:11.840
Achieving zero emissions is truly no easy feat.

00:04:14.680 --> 00:04:16.040
Many of the smaller mills

00:04:16.880 --> 00:04:18.399
Can't afford environmental equipment.

00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:21.600
President Xiao and I contacted Hongxing Mill

00:04:22.240 --> 00:04:26.120
To collect the wastewater from soaking bark

00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:29.960
And send it to Hongxing for treatment.

00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:33.240
That eased a lot of pressure on the small mills.

00:04:34.480 --> 00:04:35.480
All these things

00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:38.600
We've been doing quietly without fanfare.

00:04:39.040 --> 00:04:42.920
But being quiet doesn't mean no one notices.

00:04:43.680 --> 00:04:45.040
The people know what's going on,

00:04:45.440 --> 00:04:47.480
And so do the higher-ups.

00:04:48.080 --> 00:04:50.040
Wait, are you hinting at something?

00:04:50.840 --> 00:04:51.800
A lot of things,

00:04:51.920 --> 00:04:53.080
You have to figure out yourself.

00:04:54.400 --> 00:04:57.080
Wanting to advance yourself is a good thing,

00:04:57.400 --> 00:05:00.320
But you can't rush it.

00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:03.760
Why don't you just say it directly?

00:05:03.960 --> 00:05:06.480
Director Liao is sharing life wisdom with you.

00:05:06.720 --> 00:05:08.040
Only those who understand take a half step.

00:05:08.440 --> 00:05:10.200
You haven't even taken half a step.

00:05:10.200 --> 00:05:11.760
You should learn from Director Liao

00:05:11.760 --> 00:05:13.680
And try to take at least half a step forward.

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:14.200
Boss Jiang.

00:05:14.760 --> 00:05:15.560
The director's here too.

00:05:16.240 --> 00:05:17.160
Bringing me a gift, are you?

00:05:17.720 --> 00:05:20.520
Looks like business has been good lately.

00:05:20.720 --> 00:05:21.920
Don't mock me.

00:05:22.520 --> 00:05:24.920
I've been fired. I'm barely getting by.

00:05:25.040 --> 00:05:26.200
Is the government handing out money?

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:28.720
Nothing decent ever comes out of your mouth.

00:05:29.360 --> 00:05:30.160
Recently,

00:05:30.160 --> 00:05:32.840
Our town launched a video account

00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:35.800
To promote our Xuan paper.

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:36.920
Have you followed it?

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:39.400
How many followers does it have?

00:05:39.800 --> 00:05:41.000
Can you count them on one hand?

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:41.720
Erhu,

00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:44.640
It's the internet age now.

00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:46.000
You can't be behind the times.

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:46.560
Come here.

00:05:46.560 --> 00:05:48.720
Let me show you our video account.

00:05:50.920 --> 00:05:51.720
Erhu,

00:05:51.960 --> 00:05:53.680
You should learn a thing or two from Director Liao.

00:05:54.560 --> 00:05:57.000
Yiran, I heard you've been

00:05:57.560 --> 00:05:58.840
Arranging a loan for the Xuan family.

00:05:59.560 --> 00:06:00.520
Did it go through?

00:06:01.080 --> 00:06:01.880
All done.

00:06:02.600 --> 00:06:03.760
This Paper King Competition

00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:05.440
Hit the Xuan family pretty hard.

00:06:05.640 --> 00:06:06.880
If they can't generate more revenue,

00:06:07.280 --> 00:06:08.880
A loan alone won't solve the problem.

00:06:09.600 --> 00:06:11.040
We also want to help Auntie Xu

00:06:11.040 --> 00:06:12.680
Get the e-commerce livestream going,

00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:14.320
But Auntie is just too busy.

00:06:14.320 --> 00:06:16.080
She can only livestream a few hours a day,

00:06:16.120 --> 00:06:18.160
Not even meeting the platform's required hours.

00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:20.840
My master's wife has it the hardest.

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:24.880
She handles inspections, sales, finances,

00:06:24.880 --> 00:06:25.760
And on top of that, for all those people,

00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:27.560
She cooks, cleans, and so on.

00:06:28.880 --> 00:06:29.800
Could you

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:32.000
Quietly talk to her on my behalf?

00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:34.320
I've got some orders I could give them.

00:06:34.760 --> 00:06:35.800
The profit isn't much,

00:06:36.120 --> 00:06:38.920
But at least it can cover wages and such.

00:06:39.440 --> 00:06:41.280
Then just have Xuan Yao tell her, right?

00:06:41.280 --> 00:06:42.000
No.

00:06:42.560 --> 00:06:43.920
I can't let my master find out

00:06:43.920 --> 00:06:45.440
That Xuan Yao and I are scheming behind his back.

00:06:46.640 --> 00:06:48.440
President Xiao, how loyal of you.

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:49.920
Come on, don't say that.

00:06:49.920 --> 00:06:51.000
But let me tell you,

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:52.240
If Xuan Yao can't pull it off,

00:06:52.240 --> 00:06:53.240
There's no way I can.

00:06:54.120 --> 00:06:55.520
Aren't you putting him on too high a pedestal?

00:06:56.320 --> 00:06:58.200
What, can't you manage without him?

00:06:59.120 --> 00:07:00.240
Just do me this favor.

00:07:00.640 --> 00:07:02.600
Have a proper talk with my master's wife, okay?

00:07:04.720 --> 00:07:05.520
I'll try.

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:06.760
Thank you, thank you.

00:07:15.680 --> 00:07:16.600
Zhang Du.

00:07:19.640 --> 00:07:20.800
Coming, coming, coming.

00:07:21.320 --> 00:07:22.880
I thought you weren't home.

00:07:24.240 --> 00:07:25.680
I was busy, didn't hear you.

00:07:31.480 --> 00:07:32.640
Help me unload these boxes.

00:07:34.400 --> 00:07:35.440
Unload the boxes?

00:07:35.440 --> 00:07:36.880
What's in these boxes?

00:07:38.680 --> 00:07:39.880
I'm staying with you for a few days.

00:07:40.760 --> 00:07:42.920
Staying... staying here?

00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:44.800
Which room do I get?

00:07:45.440 --> 00:07:48.000
You'll have to make do with the guest room.

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:50.120
Fine, as long as I have a place to sleep.

00:07:50.920 --> 00:07:51.720
Come on.

00:07:54.480 --> 00:07:55.320
Let me help you.

00:07:55.320 --> 00:07:56.200
Thanks.

00:07:59.800 --> 00:08:01.320
The air here is so much better.

00:08:02.880 --> 00:08:04.680
You've made this little place pretty charming.

00:08:04.680 --> 00:08:06.040
If I'd known, I would've moved in sooner

00:08:06.040 --> 00:08:07.320
And lived here with you.

00:08:07.560 --> 00:08:08.880
If you'd told me earlier,

00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:10.560
I would've tidied up better for you.

00:08:11.080 --> 00:08:12.640
This is the old Xuan family home.

00:08:12.640 --> 00:08:13.760
You're the rightful owner.

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:16.440
Come whenever you like.

00:08:17.800 --> 00:08:19.680
I'm just a passing guest.

00:08:19.680 --> 00:08:21.000
Life is but a journey.

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:22.560
Aren't we all just passing through?

00:08:23.120 --> 00:08:25.440
Meetings and partings come with fate.

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:28.000
Fate brings us together, then apart.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.360
Is this a painting by Chen Shu?

00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:31.760
The top female painter of the Qing dynasty.

00:08:32.440 --> 00:08:34.120
Your restoration work is impressive.

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:35.000
Not bad at all.

00:08:35.880 --> 00:08:36.799
Don't touch it.

00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:38.559
Why? Is there some rule about it?

00:08:39.799 --> 00:08:41.320
Yes, this is your house,

00:08:41.559 --> 00:08:44.200
But many things here belong to me.

00:08:44.440 --> 00:08:45.880
So if you want to touch my things,

00:08:45.920 --> 00:08:47.240
You have to get my permission.

00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:48.440
That's fair, isn't it?

00:08:48.440 --> 00:08:49.520
Fair enough.

00:08:49.560 --> 00:08:50.880
Can I touch it then?

00:08:50.880 --> 00:08:51.600
No.

00:08:52.760 --> 00:08:53.840
While you're staying here,

00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:55.440
I have no other requirements,

00:08:55.480 --> 00:08:57.440
Just respect each other's space.

00:08:58.280 --> 00:09:00.560
How much do you get for restoring a painting?

00:09:00.960 --> 00:09:02.320
Hard to say.

00:09:02.760 --> 00:09:03.720
Sometimes a lot,

00:09:03.920 --> 00:09:05.040
Sometimes nothing.

00:09:05.040 --> 00:09:06.480
People just pay what they think it's worth.

00:09:07.440 --> 00:09:08.840
Sometimes I work for free.

00:09:09.080 --> 00:09:11.280
Many of the paintings belong to public institutions.

00:09:11.400 --> 00:09:13.800
They have no budget for restoration.

00:09:13.960 --> 00:09:15.440
But it'd be a shame not to restore them.

00:09:16.320 --> 00:09:17.760
Your dedication

00:09:17.920 --> 00:09:19.320
Is really one of a kind.

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:21.320
What's for dinner?

00:09:21.680 --> 00:09:22.440
I don't eat after noon.

00:09:22.440 --> 00:09:24.200
You don't, but I do.

00:09:24.200 --> 00:09:25.120
Can you cook?

00:09:25.680 --> 00:09:26.520
A little.

00:09:26.520 --> 00:09:27.320
Make me something.

00:09:27.880 --> 00:09:28.800
I don't have time.

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:30.360
Order takeout yourself.

00:09:30.360 --> 00:09:31.320
You're really something.

00:09:51.760 --> 00:09:53.560
The 500,000 we got from the loan,

00:09:53.880 --> 00:09:56.120
After paying over 100,000 for materials,

00:09:56.520 --> 00:09:58.040
And the utility bills,

00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:02.360
It's barely enough for next month's wages.

00:10:02.960 --> 00:10:04.400
Without a steady income,

00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:06.400
We can't keep going like this.

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:08.920
We're just taking it day by day.

00:10:09.320 --> 00:10:11.720
When the day comes that we truly can't hold on,

00:10:11.720 --> 00:10:13.080
I'll finally be free of it.

00:10:13.640 --> 00:10:14.480
Come on.

00:10:16.960 --> 00:10:18.080
Come in, dear.

00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:21.800
Oh my, what a mess.

00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:23.240
Sorry about that.

00:10:23.240 --> 00:10:23.520
It's fine.

00:10:23.520 --> 00:10:24.280
Sorry.

00:10:28.840 --> 00:10:32.440
Auntie, these creative products,

00:10:32.440 --> 00:10:33.640
They're all made of Xuan paper?

00:10:34.040 --> 00:10:35.760
Yes, they're all Xuan paper.

00:10:36.240 --> 00:10:39.840
Xuan Yao is actually deeply attached to Xuan paper.

00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:43.840
These Xuan paper works, oil paintings, and gouaches,

00:10:44.160 --> 00:10:45.360
Were all painted by Xuan Yao.

00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:46.520
Of course,

00:10:47.400 --> 00:10:48.400
Many of these paintings

00:10:48.400 --> 00:10:51.000
Have been exhibited overseas.

00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:55.120
I really didn't expect him to paint this well.

00:10:56.480 --> 00:10:58.600
Well, you didn't know,

00:10:58.840 --> 00:11:00.520
But his master is amazing.

00:11:00.720 --> 00:11:02.240
Jiang Ziliu.

00:11:02.520 --> 00:11:03.280
That man,

00:11:03.280 --> 00:11:05.120
He may seem arrogant,

00:11:05.120 --> 00:11:07.240
A bit hard to like, right?

00:11:07.520 --> 00:11:10.000
But he really does paint beautifully.

00:11:10.400 --> 00:11:11.880
And he treats Xuan Yao

00:11:11.880 --> 00:11:14.040
Extremely well, like his own son.

00:11:14.040 --> 00:11:16.720
When they talk about Xuan paper and painting,

00:11:16.960 --> 00:11:18.680
They go on for nights on end.

00:11:19.480 --> 00:11:21.360
Yeah, I can imagine that.

00:11:22.520 --> 00:11:25.160
But Uncle Xuan says neither of them takes things seriously.

00:11:28.240 --> 00:11:30.480
Actually, when he graduated from college,

00:11:30.480 --> 00:11:31.880
He could've stayed in Beijing.

00:11:31.880 --> 00:11:34.600
Big companies in Beijing wanted to hire him.

00:11:34.720 --> 00:11:37.360
His master also wanted him to stay there.

00:11:37.520 --> 00:11:38.720
I told him too,

00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:40.760
"Don't keep worrying about your dad and me.

00:11:40.760 --> 00:11:42.400
Think about your own future."

00:11:42.640 --> 00:11:43.640
But he just wouldn't listen.

00:11:45.360 --> 00:11:46.640
Now, looking back,

00:11:46.880 --> 00:11:48.240
I don't even know

00:11:48.280 --> 00:11:51.160
If it was the right choice or not.

00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:56.360
Dear, tell me honestly,

00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:59.760
Will anyone actually buy this stuff?

00:12:01.120 --> 00:12:02.720
That depends on how he sells it.

00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:05.720
I, for one, really like them.

00:12:05.760 --> 00:12:08.360
And these days, when young people buy things,

00:12:08.360 --> 00:12:09.600
It's not really about being useful.

00:12:09.600 --> 00:12:11.800
It's more about emotional value.

00:12:11.800 --> 00:12:12.840
That's really important.

00:12:13.760 --> 00:12:15.400
Emotional value.

00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:18.360
We don't get it. We're too old.

00:12:18.360 --> 00:12:20.240
Let him be. Let him do his thing.

00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:21.640
Auntie.

00:12:22.880 --> 00:12:24.160
President Xiao came to see me.

00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:26.040
He said his handmade paper orders

00:12:26.040 --> 00:12:26.960
Are too much to handle.

00:12:26.960 --> 00:12:28.760
He wants to share some with your family.

00:12:30.520 --> 00:12:31.040
No need.

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:32.640
Thank him for me.

00:12:38.320 --> 00:12:40.520
Auntie, this...

00:12:41.520 --> 00:12:42.200
Oh, that one.

00:12:42.200 --> 00:12:43.280
It's getting thrown out. Hand it over.

00:12:43.280 --> 00:12:44.000
No, no, no.

00:12:44.200 --> 00:12:45.640
Could I keep this?

00:12:45.920 --> 00:12:46.720
You want it?

00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:48.880
If you don't mind, just take it.

00:12:49.120 --> 00:12:50.120
Thank you, Auntie.

00:12:52.640 --> 00:12:53.640
It's messy.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:54.760
Never mind.

00:12:54.760 --> 00:12:56.080
Just put them all together.

00:13:05.520 --> 00:13:06.240
These pieces here

00:13:06.240 --> 00:13:08.360
Are all based on authentic Xuan paper,

00:13:08.440 --> 00:13:10.080
Reproduced by renowned masters

00:13:10.080 --> 00:13:11.840
Using the same mineral pigments

00:13:11.840 --> 00:13:13.160
From paintings made centuries ago.

00:13:13.160 --> 00:13:15.480
Then we use top-tier laser color printing

00:13:15.480 --> 00:13:16.440
To render them.

00:13:16.560 --> 00:13:17.760
To the naked eye,

00:13:17.760 --> 00:13:18.960
They're virtually indistinguishable.

00:13:21.280 --> 00:13:22.160
Now look over here.

00:13:22.160 --> 00:13:24.440
This is our thread-bound book binding process.

00:13:25.240 --> 00:13:27.120
These photos are all from our workshop?

00:13:27.120 --> 00:13:28.520
Yes, all shot on location.

00:13:31.600 --> 00:13:33.680
At Da Ya Zhai, we've faithfully reproduced

00:13:33.680 --> 00:13:35.080
Thousands of ancient texts,

00:13:35.640 --> 00:13:37.360
Made entirely from Xuan paper.

00:13:37.720 --> 00:13:39.760
Rare ancient books throughout history

00:13:39.760 --> 00:13:40.680
Have been passed down to today,

00:13:40.680 --> 00:13:42.680
Preserving Chinese civilization and culture.

00:13:42.680 --> 00:13:44.640
We use Xuan paper, which lasts a thousand years,

00:13:44.640 --> 00:13:46.280
To carry them forward.

00:13:47.520 --> 00:13:50.680
Over here are examples of ancient book layouts.

00:13:54.920 --> 00:13:55.760
And here,

00:13:55.760 --> 00:13:57.040
This is our newly designed

00:13:57.040 --> 00:13:58.680
Casing for ancient books.

00:13:58.960 --> 00:13:59.600
Right here,

00:13:59.600 --> 00:14:00.480
We've also reproduced

00:14:00.480 --> 00:14:02.440
A complete set of the Yongle Encyclopedia.

00:14:02.560 --> 00:14:05.240
This is Da Ya Zhai's greatest treasure:

00:14:05.240 --> 00:14:07.360
The Siku Quanshu, over 30,000 volumes,

00:14:07.360 --> 00:14:08.360
Reproduced from the original.

00:14:09.680 --> 00:14:10.200
This way, please.

00:14:10.360 --> 00:14:11.720
Made with traditional Xuan paper techniques,

00:14:11.920 --> 00:14:14.200
All stored in large camphor wood cabinets,

00:14:14.360 --> 00:14:15.560
Row after row.

00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:17.560
That's the most magnificent thing of all.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:39.960
There's more inside.

00:14:39.960 --> 00:14:41.520
We can go in and take a look.

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:48.800
This way, please.

00:14:57.640 --> 00:14:59.120
This notebook is no ordinary thing.

00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:02.360
Look, the cover of this notebook

00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:04.880
Uses four layers of Xuan paper as a hard mount.

00:15:05.360 --> 00:15:06.680
Tortoise-shell style thread binding.

00:15:06.800 --> 00:15:08.320
All of these details

00:15:08.320 --> 00:15:11.080
Follow the classic Ming-era official book printing methods.

00:15:11.240 --> 00:15:13.120
It shows this person really knows his craft.

00:15:13.200 --> 00:15:15.160
But what's truly impressive

00:15:15.240 --> 00:15:16.720
Is that he isn't bound by ancient methods.

00:15:16.880 --> 00:15:17.680
Here.

00:15:18.160 --> 00:15:19.840
On the binding and color choices,

00:15:19.840 --> 00:15:21.640
He made bold subtle adjustments.

00:15:21.880 --> 00:15:22.920
Every single detail

00:15:22.920 --> 00:15:25.520
Rooted in tradition, yet still innovative.

00:15:25.800 --> 00:15:27.680
So a notebook made this way

00:15:27.720 --> 00:15:29.120
Has an overall quality

00:15:29.320 --> 00:15:31.400
That feels both stylish and high-end.

00:15:32.160 --> 00:15:33.640
Now that you mention it, it really is.

00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:35.400
We just thought it looked pretty.

00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:37.760
Didn't expect there's so much craft behind it.

00:15:37.760 --> 00:15:39.600
Hearing thunder in silence,

00:15:40.040 --> 00:15:42.040
Seeing mastery in the smallest details.

00:15:43.520 --> 00:15:44.360
Who made this?

00:15:44.640 --> 00:15:45.480
Xuan Yao.

00:15:47.360 --> 00:15:48.680
Xuan Yongnian's son.

00:15:50.160 --> 00:15:51.840
You brought this notebook to me.

00:15:52.560 --> 00:15:53.400
What's your intention?

00:15:54.840 --> 00:15:56.600
I'd like you to produce a few samples.

00:15:56.600 --> 00:15:58.760
I think this kind of notebook has a real market.

00:15:58.760 --> 00:15:59.840
I want to give it a try.

00:15:59.840 --> 00:16:01.120
You've come to the right person.

00:16:01.120 --> 00:16:02.560
For a notebook like this,

00:16:02.560 --> 00:16:04.320
If you want mass production

00:16:04.320 --> 00:16:06.120
While replicating the original quality,

00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:07.680
Forget Taohua Town,

00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:10.040
There are fewer than ten in all of China.

00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:11.280
Exactly.

00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:12.240
For something this challenging,

00:16:12.240 --> 00:16:13.800
Coming to Sister Xin is the right call.

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:15.840
But, will the cost be high?

00:16:17.920 --> 00:16:19.920
If we get bulk orders down the line,

00:16:19.920 --> 00:16:22.400
I'd like to keep the cost around 20-something yuan.

00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:24.000
Tell you what.

00:16:24.120 --> 00:16:26.320
Give this business to us,

00:16:27.080 --> 00:16:28.880
And as for the sampling cost,

00:16:29.240 --> 00:16:30.040
I'll cover it.

00:16:30.080 --> 00:16:31.600
Ms. Xin is always so generous.

00:16:31.760 --> 00:16:33.640
Any future orders, I'll come to you.

00:16:33.640 --> 00:16:34.320
This notebook

00:16:34.320 --> 00:16:36.000
Has real original design value.

00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:38.000
So you'll need to go see Xuan Yao again,

00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:39.200
And get his authorization.

00:16:39.440 --> 00:16:40.360
No problem with that.

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:42.280
My original purpose in doing this

00:16:42.280 --> 00:16:43.720
Was to help the Xuan family.

00:16:43.960 --> 00:16:46.720
You know about the Paper King Contest incident.

00:16:46.720 --> 00:16:48.760
It hit the Xuan family pretty hard.

00:16:49.440 --> 00:16:51.920
And they're national intangible heritage bearers.

00:16:51.920 --> 00:16:54.320
Of course our government should help and support them.

00:16:55.360 --> 00:16:56.400
What you mean is,

00:16:56.600 --> 00:16:58.960
If future orders reach a real volume,

00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:00.520
I should use the Xuan family's paper.

00:17:02.120 --> 00:17:02.960
No problem.

00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:04.720
Xuan Yongnian is someone our chairman

00:17:04.720 --> 00:17:05.920
Deeply respects.

00:17:06.040 --> 00:17:08.160
As long as your client can handle the budget,

00:17:08.839 --> 00:17:09.839
The Xuan family will be the first choice.

00:17:11.359 --> 00:17:12.040
Thank you, Sister Xin.

00:17:12.319 --> 00:17:13.119
Thank you, Sister Xin.

00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:17.920
This tree is huge.

00:17:19.520 --> 00:17:20.560
Master told me

00:17:20.800 --> 00:17:21.839
This blue sandalwood tree

00:17:21.839 --> 00:17:23.760
Is over 300 years old.

00:17:24.359 --> 00:17:25.520
Over 300 years.

00:17:29.200 --> 00:17:30.000
Zhang Du.

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:33.160
These antiques must be pretty old, huh?

00:17:33.320 --> 00:17:35.520
Yeah, they've all been around a while.

00:17:35.640 --> 00:17:38.440
This one's pre-Liberation, about a hundred years.

00:17:40.120 --> 00:17:40.880
Wow.

00:17:40.880 --> 00:17:42.880
Your little courtyard is so dreamy.

00:17:43.400 --> 00:17:44.400
It's really nice.

00:17:46.720 --> 00:17:47.800
Is Xuan Yao here?

00:17:48.480 --> 00:17:49.680
He's still sleeping.

00:17:58.360 --> 00:17:59.880
Still sleeping at this hour?

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.040
He says it's his secret to good health.

00:18:11.600 --> 00:18:12.400
Sorry about this.

00:18:12.640 --> 00:18:13.560
Last night, Xuan Yao

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:14.880
Had some friends over here.

00:18:15.400 --> 00:18:16.440
Let me tidy up.

00:18:16.440 --> 00:18:17.760
Please, have a seat.

00:18:19.360 --> 00:18:22.240
Such a nice courtyard, and he trashed it.

00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:23.200
Honestly...

00:18:23.360 --> 00:18:24.360
It's really a bit...

00:18:24.800 --> 00:18:25.480
Let me do it, let me.

00:18:25.480 --> 00:18:26.760
I'll boil some water for you first.

00:18:29.800 --> 00:18:30.240
I...

00:18:34.000 --> 00:18:36.760
Xuan Yao used my iron kettle for rice wine!

00:18:37.040 --> 00:18:39.000
I've been seasoning this kettle for a year and a half.

00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:40.600
It's completely ruined!

00:18:41.200 --> 00:18:42.440
I have to wash it right now.

00:18:42.440 --> 00:18:43.000
It's fine, it's fine.

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:43.760
We won't drink it, no, no.

00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:44.840
It's not about whether you drink.

00:18:44.840 --> 00:18:46.080
If I don't clean it now,

00:18:46.080 --> 00:18:47.360
The kettle will be ruined.

00:18:47.360 --> 00:18:49.240
Uh, Taozi, you go wash it.

00:18:49.240 --> 00:18:49.880
Quick, quick, quick.

00:18:49.880 --> 00:18:50.760
Right, I'll go.

00:18:50.760 --> 00:18:51.640
You two talk.

00:18:52.920 --> 00:18:53.800
Wash it thoroughly.

00:18:53.800 --> 00:18:54.720
Don't worry.

00:19:08.520 --> 00:19:09.920
And this guy claims to care about health?

00:19:09.920 --> 00:19:11.080
Really unbelievable.

00:19:12.880 --> 00:19:15.320
Remember the interview from last time?

00:19:16.320 --> 00:19:18.840
You said you'd painted murals,

00:19:18.840 --> 00:19:20.800
And done traditional restoration work.

00:19:21.520 --> 00:19:24.480
You wanted to make the purest traditional Xuan paper,

00:19:24.560 --> 00:19:27.040
So you learned paper-scooping from Master Xuan, right?

00:19:27.280 --> 00:19:28.080
That's right.

00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:31.000
Can I continue interviewing you?

00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:33.560
Sure, I'd be honored.

00:19:33.560 --> 00:19:34.480
Come, sit.

00:19:35.520 --> 00:19:37.360
This might be a bit forward,

00:19:38.080 --> 00:19:41.560
But you say you always do what you love,

00:19:41.560 --> 00:19:42.760
Which doesn't make money.

00:19:43.080 --> 00:19:44.640
So how do you make a living?

00:19:45.240 --> 00:19:48.640
I think a person's basic needs

00:19:48.720 --> 00:19:50.000
Are actually very, very few.

00:19:51.720 --> 00:19:53.720
Yeah, that makes sense.

00:19:53.720 --> 00:19:55.920
But it's hard to actually do.

00:19:58.200 --> 00:19:59.480
Why is it that someone

00:19:59.880 --> 00:20:02.040
Who just wants to do what they love

00:20:02.360 --> 00:20:03.240
Finds it so difficult?

00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:08.600
Have you ever thought about it?

00:20:11.280 --> 00:20:13.000
Because I'm not living for myself alone.

00:20:13.280 --> 00:20:15.120
There are many choices we're forced to make.

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:18.200
So, yeah.

00:20:18.440 --> 00:20:19.760
That's exactly why I admire you.

00:20:20.840 --> 00:20:23.480
Many "have-tos" come from kindness.

00:20:23.800 --> 00:20:27.080
We live to make others happy,

00:20:27.360 --> 00:20:28.760
Out of responsibility,

00:20:28.920 --> 00:20:30.760
Doing things we don't want to do,

00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:32.080
Compromising ourselves,

00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:34.280
Yet forgetting to be kind to ourselves.

00:20:35.520 --> 00:20:36.720
That's not freedom.

00:20:40.320 --> 00:20:41.160
You're right.

00:20:43.080 --> 00:20:43.920
I don't have much time.

00:20:45.400 --> 00:20:47.720
Which room is Xuan, Xuan Yao in?

00:20:47.760 --> 00:20:48.040
Xuan...

00:20:49.120 --> 00:20:49.960
He stays right here.

00:20:50.080 --> 00:20:50.920
Right here.

00:20:51.280 --> 00:20:51.920
Xuan Yao, Lin Yiran's here for you.

00:20:51.920 --> 00:20:53.280
Xuan Yao, Lin Yiran's here for you.

00:20:53.520 --> 00:20:54.400
She's been waiting ages. Hurry up.

00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:54.920
It's fine, it's fine, don't bother.

00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:56.080
No worries, I'll just call him.

00:20:56.080 --> 00:20:56.800
Thanks.

00:20:58.120 --> 00:20:59.360
I'll go check on my kettle.

00:20:59.520 --> 00:21:00.520
You two talk.

00:21:01.640 --> 00:21:02.440
Xuan Yao.

00:21:04.040 --> 00:21:04.840
Xuan...

00:21:06.080 --> 00:21:06.880
Xuan Yao.

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:08.040
Xuan Yao!

00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:11.920
I need to talk to you. Hurry up.

00:21:11.920 --> 00:21:12.920
Right now?

00:21:13.400 --> 00:21:14.200
Yes, right now.

00:21:14.360 --> 00:21:16.200
Can't you wait till I get dressed?

00:21:17.040 --> 00:21:18.040
Fine, fine, that's not important.

00:21:18.040 --> 00:21:19.480
Didn't you design a Xuan paper notebook?

00:21:19.480 --> 00:21:20.160
You remember, right?

00:21:20.280 --> 00:21:22.560
I had Dayazhai make some samples.

00:21:22.560 --> 00:21:24.280
And I want to test the market.

00:21:24.480 --> 00:21:25.200
Of course.

00:21:25.200 --> 00:21:26.560
If we get orders,

00:21:26.560 --> 00:21:28.320
Dayazhai will handle the business,

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:29.680
Using your family's paper.

00:21:29.840 --> 00:21:32.160
You'll work out the sales split between you.

00:21:32.160 --> 00:21:32.640
Okay?

00:21:32.640 --> 00:21:34.000
The Secretary and the Mayor

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:35.640
Are already out promoting it.

00:21:35.800 --> 00:21:37.440
So now I need your authorization,

00:21:37.440 --> 00:21:38.800
Because it's your original design.

00:21:38.800 --> 00:21:39.400
Got it?

00:21:39.400 --> 00:21:40.280
Here, sign.

00:21:40.840 --> 00:21:41.600
Hold on, wait a minute.

00:21:41.600 --> 00:21:42.520
Wait, hold up.

00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:43.800
Let me get this straight.

00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:45.520
So you took my design

00:21:45.520 --> 00:21:47.160
And pitched business to Dayazhai?

00:21:47.160 --> 00:21:48.640
Did you get my permission?

00:21:48.640 --> 00:21:50.080
Did you ask for my consent?

00:21:50.240 --> 00:21:51.800
Aren't I asking you right now?

00:21:51.800 --> 00:21:52.240
Right now?

00:21:52.240 --> 00:21:53.640
You call this asking my opinion?

00:21:53.640 --> 00:21:54.880
This is informing me.

00:21:55.680 --> 00:21:56.520
Come on, you're a guy.

00:21:56.520 --> 00:21:57.480
Why are you so fussy?

00:21:57.480 --> 00:21:57.960
Hurry up.

00:21:57.960 --> 00:22:00.240
I'm fussy? You're calling me fussy?

00:22:00.560 --> 00:22:01.960
From the first sentence you said

00:22:01.960 --> 00:22:02.840
The moment you walked in,

00:22:02.840 --> 00:22:05.400
Have you shown me an ounce of respect?

00:22:05.760 --> 00:22:06.920
How haven't I respected you?

00:22:06.920 --> 00:22:07.600
You respect me?

00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:08.760
You respect me? Right now,

00:22:09.280 --> 00:22:11.720
I don't even have my pants on yet.

00:22:13.280 --> 00:22:14.520
Time really is tight.

00:22:14.520 --> 00:22:15.720
Just understand, okay?

00:22:15.720 --> 00:22:16.240
Sign it and I'll leave.

00:22:16.240 --> 00:22:17.000
I can't understand.

00:22:17.000 --> 00:22:18.440
Here's the deal, please leave.

00:22:18.440 --> 00:22:19.000
Thank you very much.

00:22:19.000 --> 00:22:20.440
Shut the door on your way out, okay?

00:22:22.840 --> 00:22:24.200
How about this, I'll apologize, okay?

00:22:24.200 --> 00:22:25.320
Sign it, and I'll go.

00:22:25.320 --> 00:22:27.200
You go out, then we'll talk properly.

00:22:30.560 --> 00:22:31.680
So fussy.

00:22:34.640 --> 00:22:35.600
I'm fussy?

00:22:56.200 --> 00:22:58.920
Expanding the Xuan paper notebook market, I accept.

00:22:59.400 --> 00:23:01.840
But whether Dayazhai gets the business

00:23:01.960 --> 00:23:03.840
That's my call, not yours.

00:23:06.840 --> 00:23:09.640
They're willing to provide samples for free first.

00:23:09.640 --> 00:23:11.040
Compared to those small businesses in town,

00:23:11.040 --> 00:23:12.440
They're way more reliable.

00:23:12.600 --> 00:23:13.760
Your "reliable" and my "reliable"

00:23:13.760 --> 00:23:15.080
Don't seem to be the same thing.

00:23:15.200 --> 00:23:16.320
I appreciate your good intentions,

00:23:16.320 --> 00:23:17.240
But this matter,

00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:19.600
You didn't get my approval.

00:23:20.680 --> 00:23:22.440
I got Auntie's approval, you know.

00:23:22.640 --> 00:23:24.600
That's how I got this little notebook.

00:23:25.880 --> 00:23:27.680
What's the point of getting my mom's approval?

00:23:27.680 --> 00:23:29.000
Did my mom make that design?

00:23:30.480 --> 00:23:31.560
I'm telling you,

00:23:31.680 --> 00:23:34.720
I rescued it from the scrap pile.

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:36.760
Otherwise Auntie would've tossed it as trash.

00:23:36.760 --> 00:23:37.600
You know that?

00:23:37.880 --> 00:23:38.720
Still not okay.

00:23:39.960 --> 00:23:42.680
I'm the one who dug it out and arranged production,

00:23:42.680 --> 00:23:44.120
Finding all kinds of resources to promote it.

00:23:44.200 --> 00:23:46.360
If it generates profit, isn't that a good thing?

00:23:46.760 --> 00:23:48.200
That's not the point. Got it?

00:23:49.920 --> 00:23:51.120
I have to say,

00:23:51.120 --> 00:23:51.960
You're a grown man,

00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:53.560
Can you stop being so fussy?

00:23:53.560 --> 00:23:54.920
If I'm not fussy, I won't sign.

00:23:58.480 --> 00:23:59.480
Xuan Yao, listen to me.

00:23:59.480 --> 00:24:00.800
I hope you can understand,

00:24:00.800 --> 00:24:03.040
Your family's business is struggling right now.

00:24:03.120 --> 00:24:05.960
I'm investing manpower, time, and energy

00:24:05.960 --> 00:24:06.960
To get this done.

00:24:06.960 --> 00:24:08.160
I'm not doing it for myself,

00:24:08.160 --> 00:24:09.640
I'm doing it for your family, okay?

00:24:09.640 --> 00:24:11.680
Think about your parents too, alright?

00:24:12.280 --> 00:24:13.440
Then let me

00:24:13.440 --> 00:24:15.480
Restate my principles again.

00:24:16.240 --> 00:24:19.080
Using Xuan paper notebooks to develop the market,

00:24:19.160 --> 00:24:20.080
I'm in favor.

00:24:20.240 --> 00:24:21.640
I support it with both hands.

00:24:22.440 --> 00:24:23.760
Whether to use Dayazhai,

00:24:24.360 --> 00:24:25.960
That has to go through my evaluation first.

00:24:25.960 --> 00:24:27.560
If their facilities and capabilities meet the standard,

00:24:27.640 --> 00:24:28.880
Only then will I choose to use them.

00:24:28.880 --> 00:24:30.760
So this decision is mine, not yours.

00:24:30.760 --> 00:24:31.800
Do you understand?

00:24:33.800 --> 00:24:35.160
I was absolutely right.

00:24:35.600 --> 00:24:37.800
You really are fussy.

00:24:37.800 --> 00:24:38.880
Think whatever you want.

00:24:39.320 --> 00:24:40.760
Okay, okay, stop arguing, you two.

00:24:40.760 --> 00:24:41.440
Xuan Yao,

00:24:41.440 --> 00:24:43.560
There's really an urgent matter in Taolin Village waiting for us.

00:24:43.560 --> 00:24:44.320
I admit,

00:24:44.320 --> 00:24:45.840
Yiran was a bit hasty,

00:24:45.840 --> 00:24:47.280
But don't keep butting heads with her.

00:24:47.560 --> 00:24:48.440
You have no idea

00:24:48.440 --> 00:24:49.800
How much effort Yiran put

00:24:49.800 --> 00:24:51.080
Into making this happen.

00:24:51.080 --> 00:24:52.560
Wasn't it all for your family?

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:54.240
Enough, stop talking.

00:24:54.240 --> 00:24:55.240
I'm leaving, alright?

00:24:55.240 --> 00:24:56.080
I'm done with this.

00:24:56.480 --> 00:24:57.280
Don't bother seeing me out.

00:24:57.280 --> 00:24:58.080
Don't let it happen again.

00:24:58.080 --> 00:24:58.880
Don't worry,

00:24:58.880 --> 00:25:00.480
I'd never come to you, even if it killed me.

00:25:00.600 --> 00:25:01.880
Don't be so absolute.

00:25:02.080 --> 00:25:03.640
We're bound to run into each other.

00:25:03.760 --> 00:25:04.800
You'll definitely need me for something.

00:25:04.800 --> 00:25:05.400
I'm telling you,

00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:06.800
I will never come to you.

00:25:07.760 --> 00:25:09.040
Want me to call you a cab?

00:25:19.760 --> 00:25:20.960
I was clearly helping him

00:25:20.960 --> 00:25:22.080
And ended up furious instead

00:25:22.080 --> 00:25:23.200
Why did I even bother?

00:25:23.320 --> 00:25:25.120
As if I was scheming against him

00:25:25.480 --> 00:25:26.560
Forget about someone like that

00:25:26.560 --> 00:25:28.120
Working with him would be endless trouble

00:25:28.320 --> 00:25:29.240
Calm down

00:25:29.240 --> 00:25:30.080
Let me tell you

00:25:30.360 --> 00:25:31.560
A man with no temper, no character

00:25:31.560 --> 00:25:32.600
He'll never become a master

00:25:32.800 --> 00:25:34.360
Look how bad things are at his place

00:25:34.920 --> 00:25:35.720
Still,

00:25:36.560 --> 00:25:38.520
I really admire Xuan Yao's talent

00:25:38.520 --> 00:25:40.440
Could we maybe talk with him again?

00:25:40.440 --> 00:25:41.400
I'll go with you

00:25:41.400 --> 00:25:42.240
No way

00:25:42.280 --> 00:25:43.600
I won't go see him even if it kills me

00:25:51.840 --> 00:25:52.720
Is it ready yet?

00:25:53.920 --> 00:25:55.120
I'm starving to death here

00:25:55.120 --> 00:25:57.320
We've got gas and an induction stove right here

00:25:57.320 --> 00:25:59.040
But you insist on setting up this rack

00:25:59.040 --> 00:26:00.320
Grilling and fussing over here

00:26:00.440 --> 00:26:01.200
Why on earth?

00:26:01.200 --> 00:26:02.120
I really can't figure it out

00:26:02.120 --> 00:26:03.640
Are you cultivating immortality or something?

00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:06.120
Back to basics, don't you get it?

00:26:06.400 --> 00:26:07.160
Only this way

00:26:07.160 --> 00:26:09.000
Can you taste the true flavor of the ingredients

00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:11.040
Come on, I'm just having noodles

00:26:11.040 --> 00:26:13.000
What true flavor do I need?

00:26:13.000 --> 00:26:14.200
Good food is worth the wait

00:26:14.880 --> 00:26:16.400
It's just like making Xuan paper

00:26:16.400 --> 00:26:18.760
108 steps, and not one can be skipped

00:26:19.440 --> 00:26:20.880
You've gone obsessed, haven't you?

00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:22.720
Bringing up paper no matter what

00:26:23.040 --> 00:26:25.120
What does this have to do with paper?

00:26:25.680 --> 00:26:26.880
It has everything to do with it

00:26:26.960 --> 00:26:28.200
And I'll tell you why

00:26:28.200 --> 00:26:29.120
What I want to make

00:26:29.120 --> 00:26:31.600
Is true traditional ancient-method paper

00:26:31.960 --> 00:26:32.800
Hold on a second

00:26:32.800 --> 00:26:34.960
I'm hearing something off in what you said

00:26:35.440 --> 00:26:37.560
Are you saying what our family makes

00:26:38.080 --> 00:26:39.400
Isn't ancient-method paper?

00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:45.040
It's lost its essence.

00:26:45.960 --> 00:26:47.000
Lost what essence?

00:26:49.120 --> 00:26:51.840
Did the ancients use machinery to make paper?

00:26:52.040 --> 00:26:53.440
Did they use electricity?

00:26:53.520 --> 00:26:55.000
No, they didn't. Why?

00:26:57.320 --> 00:27:00.760
It's like, originally they pounded by hand,

00:27:01.160 --> 00:27:02.360
But now they pound by electric power.

00:27:02.360 --> 00:27:03.600
And back in the day,

00:27:03.760 --> 00:27:06.160
Paper stacks were pressed with stone slabs.

00:27:06.320 --> 00:27:08.480
Now they use mechanical jacks.

00:27:08.480 --> 00:27:10.200
Originally, paper was dried in sunlight.

00:27:10.200 --> 00:27:12.040
Now it's electric heated drying walls.

00:27:12.040 --> 00:27:13.280
Details like these,

00:27:13.280 --> 00:27:14.640
And so on and so forth.

00:27:14.840 --> 00:27:16.400
It fits that old saying perfectly:

00:27:16.600 --> 00:27:19.440
"A tiny error leads to a huge mistake."

00:27:21.200 --> 00:27:22.760
I don't quite get it.

00:27:22.760 --> 00:27:26.880
What's wrong with using modern machinery?

00:27:27.040 --> 00:27:30.280
Xuan paper's materials come from nature.

00:27:30.520 --> 00:27:32.600
So the craft of making Xuan paper

00:27:32.600 --> 00:27:34.480
Should follow nature's laws too.

00:27:35.080 --> 00:27:37.800
What it experiences is the emotional bond

00:27:37.800 --> 00:27:39.040
Between craftsman and paper.

00:27:39.040 --> 00:27:41.600
That's what gives Xuan paper its soul.

00:27:41.640 --> 00:27:43.720
As they say, "The Dao follows nature."

00:27:44.120 --> 00:27:46.440
Let me feel the soul of this Xuan paper.

00:27:47.720 --> 00:27:49.280
So what you mean is,

00:27:49.400 --> 00:27:51.520
In all 108 steps of papermaking,

00:27:51.520 --> 00:27:52.320
Not a single stage

00:27:52.320 --> 00:27:54.240
Can involve modern techniques.

00:27:54.240 --> 00:27:54.840
Right?

00:27:54.840 --> 00:27:57.640
That's true traditional Xuan paper.

00:27:57.840 --> 00:27:58.640
Exactly.

00:28:00.240 --> 00:28:01.040
Master Zhang,

00:28:01.320 --> 00:28:02.240
Let me ask you this.

00:28:02.320 --> 00:28:04.040
I've got a question for you.

00:28:04.440 --> 00:28:07.000
If you went by your idea

00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:09.480
To make this truly ancient Xuan paper,

00:28:09.480 --> 00:28:10.680
How long would it take?

00:28:10.720 --> 00:28:12.480
At least a year.

00:28:12.480 --> 00:28:13.320
And how much would you sell it for?

00:28:13.320 --> 00:28:15.120
Talking money with me is vulgar.

00:28:15.120 --> 00:28:15.960
Vulgar or not,

00:28:15.960 --> 00:28:17.160
Once you finish, do you just keep it at home,

00:28:17.160 --> 00:28:17.720
Sitting there staring at it?

00:28:17.720 --> 00:28:18.880
Put it on display at home,

00:28:18.880 --> 00:28:20.240
Look at it every day and worship it?

00:28:20.360 --> 00:28:21.400
Aren't you going to sell it?

00:28:22.360 --> 00:28:23.280
I haven't decided yet.

00:28:23.440 --> 00:28:25.600
Probably around 5,000 at least.

00:28:25.720 --> 00:28:27.440
A whole year for around 5,000?

00:28:27.440 --> 00:28:27.880
Okay.

00:28:27.880 --> 00:28:29.440
That's only about 400 a month.

00:28:29.440 --> 00:28:30.600
What are you gonna eat and drink?

00:28:30.600 --> 00:28:32.040
Live on thin air?

00:28:32.160 --> 00:28:33.640
What I want to discuss with you is

00:28:33.640 --> 00:28:35.720
How to make a truly traditional

00:28:35.720 --> 00:28:36.760
Ancient-method paper.

00:28:37.000 --> 00:28:37.840
Okay, okay, okay.

00:28:38.200 --> 00:28:40.200
I understand and respect that.

00:28:40.200 --> 00:28:42.840
I'll even ask my ancestors to bless you.

00:28:42.920 --> 00:28:44.680
But right now I'm just too hungry.

00:28:44.680 --> 00:28:45.880
I've got no energy to argue with you.

00:28:45.880 --> 00:28:47.400
Check if my noodles are done.

00:28:47.400 --> 00:28:48.200
Are they ready?

00:28:48.360 --> 00:28:50.720
Don't worry, they'll be delicious.

00:28:56.880 --> 00:28:58.960
Wait, wait, how is it burnt?

00:28:59.120 --> 00:29:00.040
It's burnt.

00:29:01.320 --> 00:29:03.280
Didn't you say you could cook?

00:29:04.760 --> 00:29:06.400
I'd better just order takeout.

00:29:22.720 --> 00:29:23.720
Let me take this call.

00:29:28.640 --> 00:29:29.560
I don't know.

00:29:31.040 --> 00:29:31.840
It wasn't me.

00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:34.520
Okay.

00:29:37.200 --> 00:29:38.000
Taozi.

00:29:39.480 --> 00:29:42.880
Did you pitch Xuan paper notebooks

00:29:42.880 --> 00:29:44.320
To Zhongrui Deying International School?

00:29:44.320 --> 00:29:45.000
No, I didn't.

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:46.360
Didn't you say you were dropping it?

00:29:47.200 --> 00:29:48.840
Ms. Xin just asked me about it.

00:29:48.960 --> 00:29:50.800
They want to order Xuan paper notebooks.

00:29:50.840 --> 00:29:52.600
Ms. Xin thought I recommended them.

00:29:52.840 --> 00:29:53.680
Why would I dig my own grave?

00:29:53.680 --> 00:29:54.760
Am I out of my mind?

00:29:56.160 --> 00:29:57.120
Oh, I just remembered.

00:29:57.760 --> 00:29:59.320
I gave some to Secretary Peng and the mayor too.

00:30:00.640 --> 00:30:01.440
Lin Yiran.

00:30:02.320 --> 00:30:02.880
Yes?

00:30:03.480 --> 00:30:05.040
Hurry, stop eating, come with me.

00:30:05.240 --> 00:30:05.960
What's going on?

00:30:05.960 --> 00:30:06.880
The Secretary wants to see you.

00:30:07.520 --> 00:30:08.320
Wait, what?

00:30:08.480 --> 00:30:10.360
Isn't the Secretary still in the leadership meeting?

00:30:10.360 --> 00:30:11.120
Taozi.

00:30:11.760 --> 00:30:12.840
The Xuan paper notebook thing,

00:30:12.840 --> 00:30:14.040
Were you involved in it too?

00:30:14.160 --> 00:30:14.760
Mayor.

00:30:14.760 --> 00:30:15.720
Didn't I give you one as well?

00:30:15.720 --> 00:30:16.120
You did?

00:30:16.120 --> 00:30:17.080
It was all my idea.

00:30:17.880 --> 00:30:19.640
Because of your bright idea,

00:30:19.840 --> 00:30:20.520
The Secretary is now...

00:30:21.600 --> 00:30:22.360
Come on, let's go.

00:30:23.800 --> 00:30:24.560
Hurry up, hurry.

00:30:30.600 --> 00:30:31.680
If you don't mess around, you won't get hurt.

00:30:32.280 --> 00:30:33.720
But you all just keep at it.

00:30:38.080 --> 00:30:40.760
I knew it. Sooner or later, you'll be the death of me.

00:30:41.400 --> 00:30:42.320
You don't need to worry.

00:30:42.400 --> 00:30:43.480
If anything happens, I'll take the blame.

00:30:43.760 --> 00:30:44.960
Hello, Deputy Mayor Luo. Hello.

00:30:45.120 --> 00:30:46.160
Hurry up.

00:30:51.440 --> 00:30:52.160
Okay, okay.

00:30:52.160 --> 00:30:53.040
I'll be right over.

00:30:55.840 --> 00:30:56.720
You two, head over to the meeting room.

00:30:56.720 --> 00:30:57.800
Five hundred copies, right?

00:30:58.960 --> 00:31:00.040
Which company are you from?

00:31:01.200 --> 00:31:03.040
Renyi Tang Cultural Training Company.

00:31:03.520 --> 00:31:04.240
Got it.

00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:05.240
How about this?

00:31:05.240 --> 00:31:05.840
Hello?

00:31:05.840 --> 00:31:07.000
I'll give you the contact for the

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:07.560
Secretary Chen.

00:31:07.560 --> 00:31:08.520
Notebook manufacturer.

00:31:08.520 --> 00:31:10.320
We're truly honored.

00:31:10.320 --> 00:31:11.760
This time, President An

00:31:11.760 --> 00:31:13.880
Personally promoted us.

00:31:15.800 --> 00:31:17.240
We will definitely

00:31:18.400 --> 00:31:20.480
Push the follow-up work forward properly.

00:31:20.600 --> 00:31:22.640
We won't let you down.

00:31:22.640 --> 00:31:23.680
All right, Secretary Chen.

00:31:23.920 --> 00:31:24.680
Yes, yes, yes.

00:31:24.680 --> 00:31:25.600
Thank you, thank you.

00:31:25.600 --> 00:31:26.840
Thanks for your support.

00:31:26.840 --> 00:31:27.760
I'll hang up now.

00:31:27.840 --> 00:31:28.640
All right.

00:31:29.840 --> 00:31:31.480
Lin Yiran, Taozi.

00:31:31.800 --> 00:31:33.680
Last week, I went to a meeting in the city.

00:31:33.800 --> 00:31:36.240
I saw President An chairing the meeting.

00:31:36.720 --> 00:31:38.800
So I gave one of our Xuan paper notebooks

00:31:38.800 --> 00:31:40.320
To President An as a gift.

00:31:40.800 --> 00:31:43.720
President An really loved our notebook.

00:31:43.960 --> 00:31:46.280
At last week's provincial trade fair,

00:31:46.400 --> 00:31:47.960
President An personally

00:31:47.960 --> 00:31:50.120
Brought this Xuan paper notebook along

00:31:50.200 --> 00:31:51.560
And promoted it for us.

00:31:51.560 --> 00:31:52.480
You know what?

00:31:52.560 --> 00:31:53.520
At the venue,

00:31:53.520 --> 00:31:55.520
Many companies and organizations

00:31:55.760 --> 00:31:57.560
Showed strong interest.

00:31:57.560 --> 00:31:59.800
My phone has been ringing off the hook.

00:32:01.360 --> 00:32:02.160
Look at this.

00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:03.720
Lin Yiran.

00:32:03.760 --> 00:32:04.840
In less than half an hour,

00:32:04.840 --> 00:32:06.120
I've already got orders for over 20,000 copies.

00:32:06.120 --> 00:32:06.800
Right?

00:32:06.800 --> 00:32:08.000
Ms. Xin's side has even more.

00:32:08.320 --> 00:32:09.280
That's wonderful.

00:32:14.720 --> 00:32:15.920
She's stunned with joy.

00:32:17.120 --> 00:32:19.080
She's so happy she hasn't snapped out of it.

00:32:19.320 --> 00:32:20.680
Don't just get carried away.

00:32:21.000 --> 00:32:22.480
You two young ladies

00:32:22.560 --> 00:32:24.640
Need to coordinate Daya Studio

00:32:24.840 --> 00:32:27.240
And the Xuan Family Paper Mill properly.

00:32:27.640 --> 00:32:29.720
Ensure quality and deliver on time.

00:32:29.720 --> 00:32:30.520
Got it.

00:32:31.560 --> 00:32:32.200
Understood.

00:32:33.040 --> 00:32:33.600
Understood.

00:32:34.200 --> 00:32:34.880
Yiran.

00:32:35.040 --> 00:32:36.360
This work cannot be taken lightly.

00:32:36.360 --> 00:32:37.320
If something goes wrong,

00:32:37.400 --> 00:32:39.040
We won't be able to answer to our superiors.

00:32:39.400 --> 00:32:41.240
Okay, okay, okay.

00:32:44.840 --> 00:32:46.120
Can you please not make me

00:32:46.120 --> 00:32:48.000
Fall into Xuan Yao's hands again?

00:32:48.560 --> 00:32:50.840
If you ask me, you two are a karmic mess.

00:32:51.560 --> 00:32:53.880
At a time like this, can you stop talking nonsense?

00:32:54.320 --> 00:32:55.360
I won't put you in a tough spot.

00:32:55.360 --> 00:32:57.200
I'll just call him myself.

00:32:59.960 --> 00:33:00.560
Sis.

00:33:02.240 --> 00:33:03.720
Give me the phone number.

00:33:03.720 --> 00:33:05.480
He won't answer your call.

00:33:05.560 --> 00:33:06.760
Sis to the rescue, as always.

00:33:07.840 --> 00:33:08.640
Sis, I'll send it to you.

00:33:16.320 --> 00:33:17.000
Hello?

00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:20.640
Hello, is this Xuan Yao?

00:33:20.800 --> 00:33:21.720
What is it?

00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:22.560
This is...

00:33:22.560 --> 00:33:23.320
Sis, just ignore him.

00:33:23.320 --> 00:33:24.320
That's his ringback tone.

00:33:26.600 --> 00:33:27.560
Who said it was a ringtone?

00:33:27.560 --> 00:33:28.560
Lin Yiran, right?

00:33:31.040 --> 00:33:32.240
Hello, Xuan Yao.

00:33:32.280 --> 00:33:33.680
I'm the general manager of Dayazhai.

00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:34.560
My name is Xin Ran.

00:33:34.560 --> 00:33:36.880
I'd like to discuss something this afternoon.

00:33:36.880 --> 00:33:38.480
Would it be convenient if I came over?

00:33:38.600 --> 00:33:40.880
I'm busy this afternoon. I'm going hill-running.

00:33:41.280 --> 00:33:41.960
Running?

00:33:41.960 --> 00:33:43.720
You want to talk about the xuan paper notebooks, right?

00:33:43.720 --> 00:33:45.480
Send Lin Yiran over this afternoon.

00:33:45.960 --> 00:33:46.800
Xuan Yao, yes,

00:33:49.640 --> 00:33:51.000
But as I was saying,

00:33:51.040 --> 00:33:52.400
It has to be you.

00:33:54.640 --> 00:33:56.200
What if I have old Mr. Xuan

00:33:56.200 --> 00:33:57.640
And Auntie Xu talk to him?

00:33:57.720 --> 00:33:58.640
Oh, please.

00:33:58.760 --> 00:34:00.280
If Xuan Yao listened to his parents,

00:34:00.280 --> 00:34:01.760
He wouldn't have been kicked out.

00:34:02.080 --> 00:34:03.320
If you stir up more conflict,

00:34:03.320 --> 00:34:04.280
It'll be a real mess to clean up.

00:34:05.200 --> 00:34:07.240
Right now, sixteen clients

00:34:07.240 --> 00:34:08.760
Are waiting to sign agreements with us.

00:34:08.760 --> 00:34:10.320
Director Ge from your town office

00:34:10.320 --> 00:34:11.880
Called me again today

00:34:11.880 --> 00:34:13.360
To coordinate the timing of these agreements.

00:34:13.800 --> 00:34:16.040
I stalled, saying finance was in Shanghai,

00:34:16.040 --> 00:34:17.040
And pushed the signing to Monday.

00:34:17.560 --> 00:34:19.320
But tomorrow is Monday already.

00:34:19.320 --> 00:34:20.520
We can't put it off any longer.

00:34:20.920 --> 00:34:22.239
This has to be resolved.

00:34:22.280 --> 00:34:24.040
Do you understand the situation we're in?

00:34:24.280 --> 00:34:25.920
This isn't just about whether Sister Xin and the Xuan family

00:34:25.920 --> 00:34:27.440
Can take on these orders anymore.

00:34:27.600 --> 00:34:28.480
These orders

00:34:28.480 --> 00:34:30.920
Were all brought to you personally by President An.

00:34:31.440 --> 00:34:32.520
If something really goes wrong,

00:34:32.760 --> 00:34:34.560
How is President An supposed to explain to everyone?

00:34:34.920 --> 00:34:36.159
What about Secretary Chen?

00:34:36.159 --> 00:34:37.280
What about Secretary Peng?

00:34:37.679 --> 00:34:39.199
Don't you want this to work out?

00:34:41.199 --> 00:34:42.360
Fine, I get it.

00:34:42.800 --> 00:34:43.679
I'll go.

00:34:43.920 --> 00:34:45.360
I'll go, okay?

00:34:49.239 --> 00:34:51.280
What did he just say he was doing?

00:34:52.280 --> 00:34:53.080
Something like...

00:34:53.480 --> 00:34:54.280
Hill-running.

00:35:11.800 --> 00:35:12.600
You're here.

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:15.720
Not bad.

00:35:16.600 --> 00:35:17.400
Waiting for me?

00:35:21.520 --> 00:35:24.760
I climb hills with an engine, you do it on legs?

00:35:31.120 --> 00:35:33.840
Didn't know you were into cycling.

00:35:34.640 --> 00:35:35.600
Pretty wild.

00:35:45.720 --> 00:35:47.640
Come on, keep up, keep up.

00:35:48.080 --> 00:35:48.840
You can do it.

00:35:49.520 --> 00:35:50.800
Speed, speed, speed!

00:35:51.160 --> 00:35:51.800
Push it!

00:35:54.480 --> 00:35:55.800
Faster, faster, faster!

00:35:58.000 --> 00:35:58.800
That's enough.

00:35:59.520 --> 00:36:00.400
I'll take you...

00:36:01.080 --> 00:36:02.520
To one of my secret spots.

00:36:04.240 --> 00:36:04.960
Stay close to me.

00:36:13.480 --> 00:36:14.720
Just as I thought.

00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:17.680
You like wild stuff just like me.

00:36:18.480 --> 00:36:20.600
Don't lump me in with you.

00:36:20.640 --> 00:36:22.000
We're not the same kind of people.

00:36:24.800 --> 00:36:26.320
You don't even have a carbon frame.

00:36:26.320 --> 00:36:27.480
Nobody's calling you a noob.

00:36:28.280 --> 00:36:29.960
You're not necessarily faster than me.

00:36:29.960 --> 00:36:31.840
Your mouth really runs faster than your brain.

00:36:32.080 --> 00:36:32.880
Mine has a...

00:36:33.080 --> 00:36:34.640
Four-cylinder pure mechanical engine.

00:36:34.640 --> 00:36:36.320
How do your two legs compare to that?

00:36:41.160 --> 00:36:42.320
Let's talk business.

00:36:43.000 --> 00:36:45.200
Right now, over a dozen vendors

00:36:45.200 --> 00:36:47.280
Are interested in ordering your Xuan paper notebooks.

00:36:47.400 --> 00:36:49.160
If the orders keep coming in,

00:36:49.160 --> 00:36:50.200
Just this one item alone

00:36:50.240 --> 00:36:53.000
Could keep the Xuan family running steadily.

00:36:53.440 --> 00:36:54.720
If you're interested,

00:36:54.720 --> 00:36:56.280
You can talk it over with Xin Ran.

00:36:56.360 --> 00:36:57.480
Well, congratulations.

00:36:57.920 --> 00:36:59.120
I'm not interested.

00:36:59.800 --> 00:37:01.120
Hey, are you being difficult?

00:37:02.200 --> 00:37:03.640
I'm actually out of energy.

00:37:04.280 --> 00:37:05.320
Why don't you give me a push?

00:37:06.480 --> 00:37:07.680
Get this straight.

00:37:07.800 --> 00:37:09.840
I'm the one helping your family here.

00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:11.720
Xuan Yao, don't push it.

00:37:11.920 --> 00:37:13.160
How am I pushing it?

00:37:14.400 --> 00:37:16.840
You did the talking, you did the work,

00:37:17.120 --> 00:37:18.440
And you made all the decisions.

00:37:18.720 --> 00:37:20.080
So tell me, how am I pushing it?

00:37:21.520 --> 00:37:23.320
Fine, then tell me, what do you want?

00:37:23.640 --> 00:37:24.440
Lin Yiran,

00:37:25.320 --> 00:37:27.120
Can you stop always using

00:37:27.320 --> 00:37:29.320
This high-pressure, aggressive tone

00:37:29.320 --> 00:37:30.440
When you talk to me?

00:37:30.760 --> 00:37:31.880
Can't you try a different approach?

00:37:31.880 --> 00:37:34.240
Like, maybe begging me?

00:37:38.120 --> 00:37:38.640
Where are you going?

00:37:38.640 --> 00:37:39.720
Don't leave!

00:37:41.360 --> 00:37:42.400
Fine, I'll agree, okay?

00:37:43.960 --> 00:37:44.760
But...

00:37:45.200 --> 00:37:46.840
I have to tour Xin Ran's factory first.

00:37:47.480 --> 00:37:48.800
If their replica version

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:50.720
Can match my original exactly,

00:37:51.040 --> 00:37:52.040
Then I'll work with her.

00:37:54.760 --> 00:37:56.160
Did I say I was leaving?

00:37:57.640 --> 00:37:58.520
I'm taking a leak.

00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:01.800
Fine.

00:38:01.800 --> 00:38:03.120
Come on, give me a push.

00:38:04.080 --> 00:38:05.280
You're not gonna let it go, huh?

00:38:06.760 --> 00:38:07.640
Why don't you try it?

00:38:07.640 --> 00:38:08.520
I can push you instead.

00:38:09.360 --> 00:38:10.320
Give it a try.

00:38:10.640 --> 00:38:11.720
So childish.

00:38:12.640 --> 00:38:13.720
The view's amazing.

00:38:16.240 --> 00:38:17.040
Try it.

00:38:19.120 --> 00:38:21.000
Come on, don't be shy.

00:38:22.320 --> 00:38:23.240
Who's being shy?

00:38:26.120 --> 00:38:26.640
Come on.

00:38:27.360 --> 00:38:28.160
Stand back a bit.

00:38:28.160 --> 00:38:28.920
Okay, okay, okay.

00:38:32.880 --> 00:38:33.920
Hold on tight.

00:38:37.520 --> 00:38:38.800
Our entire production line

00:38:38.800 --> 00:38:41.240
Is digitally controlled and data-managed.

00:38:41.280 --> 00:38:42.880
Take our finished products, for example.

00:38:42.880 --> 00:38:45.160
The error rate is kept below 0.1%.

00:38:49.920 --> 00:38:51.800
Our equipment is top-of-the-line,

00:38:52.040 --> 00:38:53.840
Making us highly competitive nationwide.

00:38:59.760 --> 00:39:01.200
As for quality inspection,

00:39:01.200 --> 00:39:02.200
We have a strict system

00:39:02.200 --> 00:39:04.360
Of initial, secondary, and random checks.

00:39:04.360 --> 00:39:07.240
All in strict accordance with production standards.

00:39:07.320 --> 00:39:09.400
You can rest assured about quality control.

00:39:12.000 --> 00:39:13.360
These are the notebooks we produce.

00:39:18.160 --> 00:39:18.960
What do you think?

00:39:20.400 --> 00:39:21.240
Take another look.

00:39:21.440 --> 00:39:22.240
This way, please.

00:39:22.920 --> 00:39:23.920
Master Xuan,

00:39:24.080 --> 00:39:25.880
These are all from our Dayazhai.

00:39:25.880 --> 00:39:28.480
Ancient thread-bound books reproduced on Xuan paper.

00:39:29.080 --> 00:39:30.160
You can take a look.

00:39:31.240 --> 00:39:32.080
And over here,

00:39:32.160 --> 00:39:33.240
These are ancient books our chairman

00:39:33.240 --> 00:39:35.320
Has collected over many years.

00:39:36.240 --> 00:39:38.080
Of course, this is just a small part.

00:39:38.080 --> 00:39:39.200
Come, this way please.

00:39:40.320 --> 00:39:42.360
Let me show you the Siku Huiyao.

00:39:42.600 --> 00:39:43.280
And over here,

00:39:43.280 --> 00:39:46.120
High-precision artworks our chairman collected.

00:39:48.120 --> 00:39:50.920
These were made with traditional Xuan paper,

00:39:50.920 --> 00:39:53.600
A 1:1 reproduction of the Siku Quanshu.

00:39:55.480 --> 00:39:57.920
Come see the quality of our Dayazhai.

00:40:03.440 --> 00:40:05.880
These are our high-precision art reproductions.

00:40:17.520 --> 00:40:19.800
So? Can we do business?

00:40:23.000 --> 00:40:23.880
Let's get down to business.

00:40:31.360 --> 00:40:32.920
Master Xuan, this way, please.

00:40:32.920 --> 00:40:33.800
Let's go have a chat.

00:40:45.120 --> 00:40:46.480
The color of this cover is off.

00:40:46.840 --> 00:40:47.640
Impossible.

00:40:48.200 --> 00:40:50.000
Please compare it with the original again.

00:40:50.160 --> 00:40:50.840
No need to look.

00:40:50.840 --> 00:40:52.800
I can spot our family's paper at a glance.

00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:54.960
Is there a difference? Let me see.

00:40:55.560 --> 00:40:57.960
We specifically analyzed and calibrated the color.

00:40:58.240 --> 00:41:00.840
Whether by data or by eye,

00:41:01.040 --> 00:41:02.000
There's no problem at all.

00:41:02.120 --> 00:41:03.520
The colors look the same.

00:41:03.640 --> 00:41:05.520
Honestly, they look identical to me too.

00:41:06.760 --> 00:41:08.840
Well, they look different to me.

00:41:11.120 --> 00:41:13.720
Ordinary people have trichromatic vision,

00:41:14.440 --> 00:41:16.320
With only three types of cone cells,

00:41:16.400 --> 00:41:18.960
Seeing about one million different colors.

00:41:18.960 --> 00:41:21.320
But tetrachromats are different.

00:41:21.320 --> 00:41:22.880
They can distinguish 100 million.

00:41:23.720 --> 00:41:25.400
Of course, I'm just an ordinary person.

00:41:25.400 --> 00:41:26.400
I can't see it either.

00:41:26.400 --> 00:41:27.840
But I can sense

00:41:27.840 --> 00:41:30.160
The subtle difference between these two.

00:41:30.320 --> 00:41:31.400
Putting them side by side,

00:41:31.400 --> 00:41:34.320
This one is clearly softer and warmer.

00:41:35.240 --> 00:41:36.560
Don't look with your eyes.

00:41:36.640 --> 00:41:38.720
Use feeling, intuition.

00:41:38.880 --> 00:41:40.240
Can't you just speak plainly?

00:41:40.280 --> 00:41:41.520
Always with this airy-fairy stuff.

00:41:42.240 --> 00:41:43.360
I see it now.

00:41:44.240 --> 00:41:45.480
To the naked eye,

00:41:45.480 --> 00:41:46.840
There really is no difference.

00:41:46.840 --> 00:41:48.360
But if you feel it carefully,

00:41:48.400 --> 00:41:51.640
The original's texture and color feel finer.

00:41:53.880 --> 00:41:54.760
Master Xuan,

00:41:57.080 --> 00:41:58.640
I don't deny your expertise.

00:41:58.640 --> 00:42:00.160
I've been in high-precision printing

00:42:00.680 --> 00:42:02.240
For nearly 20 years.

00:42:02.280 --> 00:42:05.120
We have many clients from Hong Kong, China, and Japan.

00:42:05.160 --> 00:42:06.800
You know how picky they are.

00:42:07.120 --> 00:42:08.760
But every result I deliver

00:42:09.320 --> 00:42:11.360
Leaves them speechless.

00:42:12.120 --> 00:42:14.520
Have we compared with a high-precision colorimeter?

00:42:14.680 --> 00:42:16.120
We do have one,

00:42:16.760 --> 00:42:17.960
But there's no need.

00:42:18.600 --> 00:42:20.840
A color difference must exceed 13

00:42:20.840 --> 00:42:23.680
For ordinary eyes to detect it.

00:42:24.360 --> 00:42:26.840
That you've kept the color difference

00:42:26.840 --> 00:42:28.960
Within 0.25

00:42:28.960 --> 00:42:30.320
Already impresses me greatly.

00:42:30.320 --> 00:42:33.320
But if I'm not mistaken,

00:42:34.320 --> 00:42:37.200
The difference between these two should be

00:42:37.560 --> 00:42:39.320
Around 0.003.

00:42:41.720 --> 00:42:42.960
0.003.

00:42:44.240 --> 00:42:45.160
No more, no less.

00:42:45.800 --> 00:42:46.920
Exactly 0.003.

00:42:46.920 --> 00:42:48.800
Lao Huang, don't get worked up yet.

00:42:49.440 --> 00:42:51.680
There's always someone better out there.

00:42:51.680 --> 00:42:53.440
Ms. Xin, that's not the point.

00:42:54.200 --> 00:42:56.600
Do you know what a 0.003 difference means?

00:42:56.600 --> 00:42:58.280
That's on a micrometer scale.

